-- U.S. RESEARCH ROUNDUP-3M Co, Homeaway, Verastem
-- 
-- Wed Dec 17, 2014 06:23AM EST
-- None



Dec 17 (Reuters) - Wall Street securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several U.S.-listed companies, including Verastem and AMC Entertainment, on Wednesday.

HIGHLIGHTS * AMC Entertainment <AMC.N>: Stifel raises target price to $30 from $26; rating buy * Encana Corporation <ECA.N>: National Bank Financial cuts to sector perform from outperform * Homeaway <AWAY.O>: Buckingham Research starts with neutral rating; target price $32 * Verastem <VSTM.O>: Wells Fargo starts with outperform rating   Following is a summary of research actions on U.S. companies reported by Reuters on Wednesday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order. * 3M Co <MMM.N>: Bernstein raises target price to $173 from $156; rating market perform * AMC Entertainment <AMC.N>: Stifel raises target price to $30 from $26; rating buy * Boston Properties <BXP.N>: JP Morgan raises target price to $141 from $132; rating neutral * Dave & Buster's Entertainment <PLAY.O>: Stifel raises target price to $28 from $25; buy * Encana Corporation <ECA.N>: National Bank Financial cuts to sector perform from outperform * Encana Corporation <ECA.N>: National Bank Financial cuts target price to $18 from $22 * Factset Research Systems <FDS.N>: UBS raises target price to $135 from $125; neutral * Homeaway INC <AWAY.O>: Buckingham Research starts with neutral rating; target price $32 * Salix Pharmaceuticals <SLXP.O>: Canaccord Genuity raises target price to $147 from $117 * Salix Pharmaceuticals <SLXP.O>: Leerink raises target price to $127 from $108; outperform * Salix Pharmaceuticals <SLXP.O>: Mizuho Securities raises target price to $103 from $88 * Scana Corp <SCG.N>: UBS raises target price to $59 from $57; rating neutral * Symantec <SYMC.O>: William Blair cuts to market perform from outperform * Talisman Energy <TLM.N>: Raymond James raises target to $8 from $4.50; market perform * Tripadvisor Inc <TRIP.O>: Buckingham starts with neutral rating; target price $67 * Verastem <VSTM.O>: Wells Fargo starts with outperform rating * Verisk Analytics <VRSK.O>: Deutsche Bank cuts target price to $66 from $67;rating hold